==English==

===Verb===
'''cribbing'''
#Present participle of [[crib]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# The [[timbers]] used in building a crib, i.e., a heavy structure built to support an existing structure from underneath, as with a [[mineshaft]] or when raising a house off its foundation for moving to another location; [[cribwork]]. 
#:''After the Loma Prieta earthquake, they had to put cribbing under portions of the Embaracadero Freeway, for fear it would collapse.''
#:''If the structure is to be raised in place without relocation, once it is raised to the desired elevation the jacks are replaced with timber cribbing.'' -- [http://www.usace.army.mil/civilworks/cecwp/NFPC/fpslab/ace2-05.htm US Army Corps of Engineers site]
# The timbers used to support anything, as with a retaining wall, or to prop up a piece of heavy machinery.